msgid "PERSONA_1015_NAME"
msgstr "Kindred to Other Kinds"

msgid "PERSONA_1015_DESC"
msgstr "You feel natural curiosity and warmth toward cultivators of other races, and are willing to build ties across differences of origin."

msgid "PERSONA_1016_NAME"
msgstr "Hates Other Kinds"

msgid "PERSONA_1016_DESC"
msgstr "You instinctively reject cultivators of other races and find it hard to truly trust outsiders."

msgid "WORLD_INFO_RACE_TITLE"
msgstr "Race"

msgid "WORLD_INFO_RACE_NAME"
msgstr "Race"

msgid "WORLD_INFO_RACE_DESC"
msgstr "The world contains both human and yao cultivators. Yao include fox, wolf, bird, snake, turtle, and other races, each with different instincts: foxes are clever and sly, wolves are fierce hunters, birds excel at migration and scouting, snakes are patient and venomous, and turtles are long-lived and defensive. Yao can cultivate and join sects that accept them, but some sects that emphasize human rites or Confucian order do not accept yao."
